but I think this is the best quote about anthropology written:


Umesh Pandey from Karimpur, the village in Western Uttar Pradesh studied by American anthropologists since 1925, explained the feelings of the anthroplogical subject:

&quot;We want friendship, they want information; we want life-long relations, they want information; we want to think of them as part of our family, they want information. Anthropologists come and go like a dream. It is difficult to know what to like or hate. Still, we love them.&quot;
